## Summary

**{{COMPANY_NAME}}** is **{{TODO_COMPANY_ONE_LINER}}**. This plan covers the next twelve months: where we want to be, what gets us there, what we need to get it done, and the risks that could knock us off course.

The plan is read by the team, by the board, and by anyone underwriting our growth (investors, lenders, grant bodies). It is updated at every board meeting.

## Messaging

The core message is captured in the *Positioning Statement* and the *Value Proposition Document*. Every external surface — website, deck, outbound email, demo script — works from the same wording.

If a change to the messaging is proposed, the *Brand Messaging Guide* is updated first; nothing on the website or in the deck moves until the canonical message has.

## Principles

1. We act lawfully, ethically and in good faith.
2. We treat the people we work with — staff, contractors, customers, suppliers, regulators — with honesty and respect.
3. We keep records that would stand up to outside scrutiny.
4. We escalate concerns early. There is no penalty for raising a concern in good faith.
5. We review and update this policy when the business or the law changes.

## Review and updates

This document is reviewed at least annually, and whenever a change to the business or to the law makes it obsolete. The review owner is recorded in the *Domain and Account Register*.

Material changes are signed off by the board and recorded in the change log at the foot of this document.

